items.text: 新美香卤面 is darn popular!
The most valuable hawker centre ever in Singapore
Tiong Bahru Lor Mee (#01-129) is pretty good. Queue is sufficiently short too. $3 gets you fish in it.
Lau Fu Zi charkwaytiao, prawn noodles and wanton mee
No harm trying the 'lucky fried kway tiao' opposite 'lao fu zi kway tiao'... I find it better :)
Try the Yummy Thai #01-161. The Seafood fried rice is delicious.
#01-121 stall selling Fish Head Bee Hoon. Long constant Q.... Hmmm is it supposed to be bland?
I love the curry pork rice, yum yum
what's not to like! Everything is great.
Go with a group - too large of a selection of outstanding hawker food to eat by yourself!  The kway chap, rojak and kway teow are worth queuing for.
Stall 105 has delicious roasted chicken rice.
Awesome tauhuey @ Lao Ban!!!!!!!! :-) a must try!
I just had an orgasm after trying the mutton soup here LOL!
This place is filled with many amazing food stores.
Albert street prawn noodle is soooo terrible! Pls don try it unless u like ur soup bland and tasteless!

Extremely dissatisfied with Nam Sing Hokkien Mee,30 mins ago they said I was next, it's been 1 hour already but still have not arrived. And they forgot to add prawns for me even though I paid $2 more!
Must try!!! Worth to queue! Satay sauce is very nice
Probably the biggest food court I have been to so far. It's nice. Too much seafood and too few fried noodle shops for me, though. :)
Checkout upstairs for tailors, laundry service, hardware supplies, stationeries, clothes, toys, shoes, watch repair, lots more... or just for some kay poh fun.
Yummy !
Warung Pak Wahab @ #01-034
Minced Mix Noodles  #01-128  Tue - Fri : 11.00am - 8.30pm  Sat - Sun : 9.30am - 8.30pm
10 Guo tie for $4... not too oily.. Filling much.. Skin not too thick and has a crispy layer.. #01-09 .. Also try it's mee hoon kuay... Nice soup... But the kuay a little thick..
Warung Pak Wahab @unit number #01-034 selling halal malay cuisine.
New stall in town! Pretty good xiao long baos. 5 for $3.50
Pasta Manna's Spaghetti Carbonara's yummy. White cream sauce just nice & not too heavy.
#01-110 aunty oats pancakes, fresh & yum!!
Traditional Claypot rice at the end of the first row is nice.. Toa payoh Rojak at second row and long queue Kway Chap easily spotted at last row.. Mei Lock Bua long long n soursop drink too!
Please clear your own trays and plates. Reduction in cleaners meant many tables are filled with dirty plates. Do your part and be considerate. Cheers
If you're coming for supper at late night,bring ur own packet of tissue! No toilet paper provided!-.-
My fav here are wanton mee, laofuzi charkwayteow, lormee, kway chap, fishbeehoonsoup, cheechongfan w charsiew!!! All these are a MUST-TRY!!!
Good Satay by Tony Tan
Lao Fu Zi char kway tiao very shiok.
132 Mini Steamboat is a must try too! #01-132
Don't let your tourist friend go there without a local - might get lost in translation
Lee Wee and Brothers otah! Not like normal otah paste. V good after taste, leaves you wanting for more!
Oh the albert street prawn noodles ate NO GOOD!
#01-111 chuan loo bee tze char is the best tze char stall here! affordable and tasty. must order claypot liver! it is so soft and nice! worth trying!
Very legit. Recommended dishes to try in the evening include satay, char kway teow and oyster omelette. I'm told the rojak is also crazy good.
加冷广东虾面，嘉宾日夜香rojak.
Awesome 菜頭粿 at #01-156!!!! must try the black one!
Come before 9pm
mee sua near the entrance is the best ~
Try the Claypot Fish Head - #fish #fishhead #chinese #claypot
Try the Lor Mee from 新美香. Superb soup base! Add some chilli and vinegar for better taste. There's always a long queue, but it's definitely worth the wait!
Prawn noodles, satay, sugar cane drink
Bring along a box of tissues to mop your sweat, wipe off the sests & chope a table!!
Must eat 老伴 beancurd! Worth the queue.
Try the Satay With Ketupat - #satay #chicken #pork #mutton #ketupat
Soursop juice, beef noodles, Rojas, satay, western, pasta, prawn mee and wanton mee
Soo kee fishball noodles are the bomb!
Meng Kee Minced Meat Noodles (#01-103) is good! Another one of those people-queue-up popular places.
#01-45 Fatman Satay!!The absolute BEST satay in Singapore!!The meat is soooo soft and tender and juicy!The sauce is just right!!
Dong Ji Fried Kway Teow is awesomeness!
My fave stall is Ah Hock Fried Hokkien Mee. Waiting time is bet 20 to 45 mins everyday! Close on Mon. Another must eat is the Fried Oysters from $4.....
Dong Ji fried kway teow better than the lao fu zi stall's!! Try it
Joo chiat teochew porridge is a rare find in Singapore. Great tasting braised items n fresh fish in teochew steam style.
Lao Ban soyabeancurd is a MUST TRY!
现做现买猪肠粉 is super awesome! Especially the prawn one! :D
I've been here 52 times and have tried 99 dishes. We loved: 1) Sugarcane Juice @ Mei Xing Coffee #01-03 2) Soya Beancurd (Almond) @ Lao Ban Soya Beancurd #01-127. See Top 10 dishes on Foodmento:
You can get everything here. Especially recommend oyster omelette (orh lua), and goreng pisang. People also seem to enjoy the lor mee, and the rojak here. (Nam Sing Hokkien Mee also very famous)
#01-148 Steamboat, best for the fresh steam  fish.
The chee cheong fun is awesome!
Mattar Road Seafood BBQ has good crabs
Seng Kee Ngo Hiang Prawn Cracker stall at #01-29 sells value-for-money, good size and quality QQ fishballs. Bite-size: fishballs into 2 portions per piece; and Ngor Hiang into 5 portions per piece.
So much anticipation for the Lao Fu Zi char kway teow but it turns out to be disappointing. Taste too sweet and nothing really special about it.
Food;) and Lao ban
Personally I feel Blanco Court Rico Kway Chap is ok is normal.  The meat is well cook and tender. However the rest of the stuff is salty. The chilli spoilt e whole thing as it taste sour.
There's a new shop 香港幸福狐狸opening at level 2, #02-007。You might find something that would interest you.  Do take a look.
Try some Chinese snacks at Soon Huat, opposite e pasta place. Nice glutinous rice!! nice uncle and aunty!
Wanton noodles at #01-02 is Yummilicious!
Chuan Kee satay, apparently
The 132 mini steamboat is nice. Must try the herbal soup base. Best !!!
Pasta manna #01-84... Serve good pasta.. Look nice n main point is cheap..
Hougang Jing Jia Mutton Soup (#01-123) is not the Chinese herb kind (New World) but really mutton soup. Might get a little too mutton-y. Mutton is tender though and tasty. Chilli is normal. So-so.
Nam Kee Hokkien Mee is awesome. Chicken chop at Western BBQ rocks. Wanton Mee stalls next to each other facing main Rd are both great
Try the soy bean curd from 老伴.. It's different from other soy bean curd
Prepare for the Q. Esp. at char kuey teow, loh mee and the mee pok stalls. Note to myself: no vinegar for my mee pok nx time!
Lucky Char Kuey Tiao worth Q-ing. Also try e Fresh juice ice blend next to it.
Xing li cooked food #01-28 - Oyster Egg (or liat) is awesome!
Steamboat steam fish very yummy.
This is one of my favorite hawker centres in Singapore. Many delicious food can be found here, you'll be spoilt for choice!
The char siew from Roast Paradise is yummy!
Recently Lao Pan Soya Beancurd business is sooo good! Dont want to miss it! Call them to reserve!
Toa Payoh rojak~~~
Hua Kee Hougang Wanton mee!! 01-02 SO GOOOOOD!!!
Try the dessert stall #01-59 晶晶冷热甜品.. The stall with thr most hello kitty arrangment ! Best bobo cha cha mus eat hot !
Cho Kee Noodles 曹记云吞面 #01-04
#01-53 chicken chop with their famous garlic sauce Die Die must eat .
well be there food ok
Lao Fu Zi Fried Kuay Teow.. Must Try....
Mini hotpot here is super nice ^^v
Holy Grill - generous portions (choice of two sides) and tasty too
Try the Wanton Mee
#01-40鑊先生港厨 super nice.... Must try !!!
Chicken cutlet at the western food stall. Back row.
Can try if u wanna skip que, quite full a box and nice
The lor mee here is worth queuing! Mad delicious.. I never get tired of eating lor mee.
Try Dry mixed beef noodle from Ying Ying Beef Noodle (#01-83). The sauce is excellent, and dun forget to add lime for that extra zest!
J & J beef noodles
It is good
The $8 stingray is so small it's not worth it.
Lao Ban's tau huay, a MUST TRY! :)
Fancy some durian puffs? Grab 'em from 717 trading #01-100.
Banana fritters! Must try!! :-D
Mr. Wok @ #01-40 sells good zhi char. I love their crab bee hoon & mussels!
Whitley Road Big Prawn Noodles are awesome!
Damn good. Best tauhuay ever!
Whitley prawn noodles!
Lao Ban beancurd is a definite must try, Lao Fu Zi char kway teow is one of my loves. Albert street prawn noodle ain't too yummy for my liking.
Lao Fu Zhi chat kway teow totally over-rated!!
Must try blanco court food centre's kway chap!!!
Must try the grass jelly drink from #01-114. Every slip is filled with jelly
Long queue at xin MRI xiang lor mee... As always!!
For a guilty pleasure try the fried oyster omelette next to the whitley big prawn noodle store. So yummy!!!
Scold people for asking if they are still selling. Got food, got lights on, how we know u not selling?

The stall named Western Barbeque here is to die for. Their garlic sauce is amazing. Located at the back row, they are the other branch of the one at the hawker ctr at Bedok Int. Hv been loyal for yrs.
Choose from over 200 different food stalls at this giant open air complex.
The tou hua slurps ah! Must try!
01-72 Soya Beancurd really cannot make it. Totally out of taste , especially the cold one.
Must Try Lao Ban BEANCURD!!!
There's a stall that sells only satay that is near 2 Japanese food stall .... Satay not nice n must wait really long...
Perfect place to have your meals. Awesome foods.
Whitley Rd Big Prawn Noodle must eat!! 
Try the Lao Ban Beancurd - #beancurd #chinese
Western food is a must try! Awesome dishes w different sauces. V filling too!!
Try the BBQ chicken wings! It's awesome :)
This is one of the top ten hawker centres in Singapore because of the amazing amount of famous and tasty stalls here. You will find a type of food to your liking.
Mattar Road Seafood Barbecue. Blk 51, Old Airport Road Food Centre, #01-63, Singapore 390051. 8 DAYS eat - Crabs. Chilli Crab (signature) Female Crab and White Pepper Male Crab
Loh mee...
Try the wantan noodle here or crocodile meat stall. One of the best. The noodle stall need to take Q no. somemore
Tried Whitley prawns noodles. Alright but still not a good as Wah Kee big prawn noodles at Pek Kio
Best Tau Hway frm Lao pan!!!!!
Yummy roasted chicken rice! #01-119 Weng Hua Yuen Hainanese Chicken
Must tray fried prawn noodle ,famous bean curd,soup fried prawn noodle, a lot of delicious food I think in here:D
Bad service at 01-131 prawn noodle stall!
Fresh fish from Steven, beside that only crab store.
Minced pork noodle #01-124. Is a must to try if u r at old airport hawker centre.
The Char Kuey Tiao @ #01-30 is a must try!
Holy Grill's Grilled Fish with Cajun Spice just taste simply marvelous! Soft and tender meat, with great-tasting sauce. You will definitely want to come back again for more.
Since I'm queuing (always) at the stall #01-53, Western Barbeque, must try their chicken cutlet!
Try the Wanton Mee
http://mobile.aaiia.biz/ and www.aaiia.biz. Send this to 10 of your friends and get free Petrol Voucher now. Blk 351 Jurong East St. 31 01-79 S(600351) Eric Choy
Wide variety of choices. Must try Lao Fu Zi Kway Teow,  Jack's Kitchen, and Lao Ban 老伴 Soy Bean.
#01-159 Great bouncy fishballs!
To-Ricos kway chap is da bomb. Super long queue during lunch hour however.
Toa payoh rojak must try! The queue is worth it. (y) :)
The meat juicy and nicely grill
Get the rojak from TOA PAYOH ROJAK stall! Remember to add all the ingredients together e.g. Cuttlefish, century egg and taopok! Worth it!
#01-25 Kheng Hai Hui Boneless Chicken Rice roast chicken rice is yummo!
Kallang Western BBQ. Chicken Chop and cutlet sedap. ask for the garlic sauce, owners own concoction. Fu Dao satay, 40 cents a stick inclusive of its black pepper satay.
Yi Ji Hokkien Prawn Mee. Lil pricy but worth a try! Noodles are not too soft and the chili goes well with it..
Unresistable THAI food ! Like no other out there ! Recommend : all dishes ! :D Yummy Thai at #01-161 ! All the way at the right :D
Bedok 85 porridge still much better!
Try the soya beancurd
Tried rojak n lor mee.. Very nice.. But not sure if I will wait the next time round.. Q abit too long..
Back for the butter crab again. Nomnomnom.
Addicted to Lao Ban.....
Soya beancurd by Lao Pan is famous. The texture is really unique, you have to try it for yourself!
It's taste so so only
+1 for the Holy Grill. The search is over.
Lao Ban tou hua! Slurps ah!
The lor mee near the Kallang Cantonese Prawn stall is awesome! Try the Kallang Cantonese Prawn mee too!!

Chee cheong fun #01-155 is gd(: worth a try!
The next person to recommend Dong Ji fried kway teow, pse indicate the stall no. Thks.

For clothes alteration, go upstairs
LaoBan! :)
Mama Recipe Briyani Rice near Holy Grill, sedap!

Try the Wanton Mee
Awesome place for dining 
Must try the Hokkien mee, prawn noodles and beancurd. (Y)
The lor mee here is to die for. Long queues daily but entirely worthwhile.
Wantan mee: Tasted top 3 stalls here. Wantans were hard. Hua Kee #01-02 most well-rounded dish. Noodle q & fragrant, char siew tasty. Gui Hua #01-106 had most vege. Cho Kee #01-04  char siew dry

I wonder if the curry puff here taste good? I want to try but its closed today:( however, even the outdoor seat is little not clean, but it's good to have breakfast here! The weather is good today! :)
The butter crab and fried fish at the Mattar Road Seafood Barbeque is awesome. Although the availability of the fried fish depends on whether they're busy so go early.
Lao ban bean curd, black carrot cake facing the road.
#01-122 Malaysia style char siew ftw!
Nam Sing Hokkien Mee (01-32) a must try... If you can find it open
Pasta Manna...shiok! 'Nuff said.
Singpost mail box is located at the end of food centre. Entrance from Dakota flats.
The taufu fa is very nice
Best Sliced Fish soup EVERRRRRRRR (Maxwell Branch)
#01-99 Ok only. Far too salty tho! Pasir Ris Blk 444's still the best!
Mini hotpot value for $

Stall 61 yummssss
Lao ban beancurd ftw!! Not your usual beancurd pls.
If u come here often, try J & J special beef noodle, #01-162. No wait during busy hrs and very good stuff.
Wanton Mee!
Oyster Omelet
Awesome place la! Try Nam Sing Frie hokkien mee.wanton mee.lor mee.kway chap.prawn noodle.rojak.char kway tiao.fish soup all la! :)
Seriously everyone should try Dong Ji Fried Kway Tiao! My dad won't disappoint you!! :D it's worth the try!!
